  <!-- THE WIRRAL BOILER QUESTION - UNIQUE SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">WIRRAL PROPERTY KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2>Which Boiler Does Your Wirral Property Actually Need?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">The most expensive boiler installation mistake is fitting the wrong type. The Wirral's housing diversity means the answer is different depending on where you live and what your current system looks like.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH41 CH42 CH44 CH45</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Victorian Birkenhead and Wallasey. Combi or Regular?</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.5rem;line-height:1.65;">Victorian terraces in Birkenhead, Tranmere, Rock Ferry and Wallasey were built with cold water storage tanks in the loft feeding gravity systems. Before installing a combi, we check mains pressure at the incoming supply. In many properties on older Wirral streets, the mains pressure entering the property is too low for a combi to deliver satisfactory hot water flow, particularly to an upstairs bathroom. In these cases, a regular boiler with a new cylinder and retained loft tank is often the better long-term solution. Other engineers sometimes skip this check. We do not.</p>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <span style="background:#fff7ed;border:1px solid #fed7aa;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);">Combi possible if pressure adequate</span>
                <span style="background:#eff6ff;border:1px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Regular boiler often correct</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH43 CH46 CH49 CH62 CH63</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">3-Bed Semis in Prenton, Moreton and Bebington. Typically Combi.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.5rem;line-height:1.65;">The large stock of 1930s to 1970s semi-detached properties across central and south Wirral is where a standard combi replacement most often applies. These properties were built with adequate infrastructure and most have mains pressure that handles a combi boiler well. A 28kW to 32kW combi is typically the right choice for a 3-bed Prenton, Moreton or Bebington semi with one bathroom. We confirm the output calculation at the free survey.</p>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <span style="background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;">Combi typically correct</span>
                <span style="background:#fff7ed;border:1px solid #fed7aa;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);">28kW to 32kW output</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH47 CH48</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Hoylake and West Kirby Period Properties. Often System or High-Output Combi.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.5rem;line-height:1.65;">West Kirby and Hoylake have a high concentration of substantial period properties, many with original heating layouts and two or more bathrooms. A standard 28kW combi is frequently under-sized for these homes and will struggle to deliver hot water to two bathrooms simultaneously. Many West Kirby properties are better served by a 36kW to 40kW combi or, for the larger homes, a system boiler with a hot water cylinder. Additionally, coastal salt air exposure in these areas means external pipework and fittings need particular attention during an installation. We carry marine-grade fittings as standard for Hoylake and West Kirby properties.</p>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <span style="background:#eff6ff;border:1px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">System boiler often best</span>
                <span style="background:#fff7ed;border:1px solid #fed7aa;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);">36 to 40kW if combi</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH60 CH61 CH64</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Heswall, Neston and Pensby. Complex Systems Requiring Full Assessment.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.5rem;line-height:1.65;">The larger detached properties of south Wirral, particularly in Heswall, Neston, Parkgate and Pensby, have among the most complex heating arrangements on the peninsula. Multiple bathrooms, underfloor heating zones, pressurised unvented cylinders and multi-zone heating controls are common. These properties require a system boiler sized correctly for the specific load, and any unvented cylinder work requires G3 qualified engineers. All our engineers hold G3 qualification. We visit every south Wirral property before quoting because the variation between properties here is too great for remote estimates.</p>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <span style="background:#eff6ff;border:1px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">System boiler typically required</span>
                <span style="background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:999px;padding:0.2rem 0.6rem;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;">G3 qualified engineers</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="background:var(--navy);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;text-align:center;">
        <strong style="color:var(--orange);display:block;margin-bottom:0.4rem;font-size:1rem;">Get this right from the start</strong>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Fitting the wrong boiler type is the most expensive installation mistake on the Wirral. Our free survey takes around 45 minutes and gives you a fixed-price quote for the right system for your specific property.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-orange" style="color:#ffffff;">Book Free Wirral Survey</a>
