  <!-- SIGNS YOUR BOILER NEEDS REPLACING -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your Wirral Boiler Needs Replacing</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">If your boiler is over 10 years old or showing any of these signs, a replacement is worth considering. Many Wirral properties have boilers from the 1990s still running on borrowed time.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler is over 10 to 12 years old</strong><p>Modern A-rated condensing boilers operate at over 90% efficiency. A pre-2010 boiler typically runs at 65 to 70%. Replacing it is almost always more cost-effective than continued repairs, especially with the older stock common in Birkenhead and Wallasey.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Escalating repair bills</strong><p>If you are spending more than £200 to £300 per year on boiler repairs across the Wirral, replacement will pay for itself. A new boiler at £1,800 compares very favourably to three years of repair bills on an ageing unit.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Yellow or orange flame</strong><p>A healthy gas flame is blue. Yellow or orange indicates incomplete combustion and a potential carbon monoxide risk. Stop using the boiler immediately and call a <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe registered</a> engineer. If you suspect a gas emergency, call <a href="https://cadentgas.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999</a> first.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Visible corrosion or rust on the boiler casing</strong><p>External corrosion, particularly around the casing joints and flue connections, indicates moisture ingress and internal deterioration. On Wirral coastal properties especially, salt-laden air can accelerate this process on boilers located in outbuildings or on external walls.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Pressure dropping repeatedly</strong><p>A boiler that loses pressure more than once every few months has a leak somewhere in the system. In older Birkenhead and Wallasey properties with original pipework, this often signals multiple deteriorating joints rather than a single point failure.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Inconsistent hot water — some rooms fine, others cold</strong><p>If some radiators heat well but others stay cold even after bleeding, the problem is likely a failing pump or motorised valve. In systems over 15 years old this typically means the cost of repair approaches or exceeds the cost of replacement.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Benchmark certificate missing or lapsed</strong><p>A boiler without a Benchmark certificate has no documented installation. You have no warranty protection and no evidence the installation was carried out legally. A replacement gives you full documentation from day one.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Energy bills climbing without explanation</strong><p>A boiler working harder than it should burns more gas for the same heat output. If your bills have increased but usage has not changed, your boiler's efficiency is falling — the earliest warning sign before a complete failure.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Recognised two or more of these? Book a free survey across the Wirral. No obligation, no pressure.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-lg" style="background:#1a3a5c;color:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,58,92,0.4);">CALL 07399 676656</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS INCLUDED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Is Included in Your Wirral Boiler Installation</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">No hidden extras. No surprise charges on invoice day. Every item below is included in your fully fitted price.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New boiler supplied and fitted</strong><p>Your chosen boiler from Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal or Baxi. Correctly sized for your specific Wirral property at the free survey. Not an estimate — an engineer's calculation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New smart controls and programmer</strong><p>A new room thermostat and programmer installed and set up. Smart controls including Nest and Hive available on request. Required under <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/boiler-plus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Plus regulations</a>.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic system filter</strong><p>A magnetic filter fitted to capture debris before it reaches the new boiler. Required by Worcester Bosch and Vaillant to maintain warranty validity. Non-negotiable on every installation we carry out.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>System flush and inhibitor</strong><p>The heating system is flushed and dosed with corrosion inhibitor to BS 7593 standard before the new boiler is connected. Essential for protecting the new heat exchanger from day one.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas Safe and Benchmark certificates issued on the day</strong><p>Legal requirement. Both issued on installation day and sent to you by email. These protect your warranty and give you proof of a legal, compliant installation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Manufacturer warranty registered on your behalf</strong><p>We register the manufacturer warranty with Worcester Bosch or Vaillant on installation day. You receive email confirmation. A step frequently forgotten by homeowners and some installers alike.</p></div></div>
