  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Boiler Installation Wirral. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Wirral homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a new boiler cost on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A like-for-like combi boiler installation starts from £1,800 fully fitted. System boilers from £2,200. Regular boilers from £2,500. All prices include the boiler, installation, controls, magnetic filter, system flush, Benchmark certificate and Gas Safe certificate. Other Wirral installers charge upwards of £2,385 for a straight combi swap. We provide a written fixed-price quote after the free survey.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">COMBI</span>&nbsp; Can I install a combi boiler in my Birkenhead or Wallasey terrace?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Sometimes, but not always. Many Victorian and Edwardian terraces in CH41 to CH45 have mains water pressure that is too low for a combi boiler to deliver satisfactory hot water flow — particularly to an upstairs bathroom. We test mains pressure at every free survey on older Wirral properties before recommending a boiler type. Fitting the wrong type is one of the most expensive and disruptive installation mistakes.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">HESWALL</span>&nbsp; My Heswall house has three bathrooms. Do I need a special boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Almost certainly yes. A standard 28kW or 32kW combi boiler cannot deliver hot water to three bathrooms simultaneously. For properties with two or more bathrooms, we typically recommend either a higher-output combi at 36 to 40kW or a system boiler with hot water cylinder. Many Heswall and Neston homes also have unvented cylinders that require G3 qualified engineers. All our engineers hold this qualification.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">G3</span>&nbsp; What is a G3 qualification and why does it matter for Wirral properties?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>G3 is the mandatory qualification for working on unvented hot water cylinders. These mains pressure systems are common in larger properties across Heswall, West Kirby and Neston. It is illegal to install, service or repair an unvented cylinder without G3 qualification. Many plumbers and boiler installers do not hold it. All our engineers do.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TIME</span>&nbsp; How long does a boiler installation take on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A like-for-like combi boiler replacement takes 4 to 6 hours in most cases, completed in a single day. System boiler installations with a new cylinder take 1 to 2 days. Regular boiler replacements take 1 to 3 days depending on complexity. We confirm the expected duration at the free survey before booking.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">WARRANTY</span>&nbsp; What warranty comes with a new Wirral boiler installation?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Worcester Bosch and Vaillant offer up to 10-year warranties when installed by an accredited engineer and serviced annually. Ideal and Baxi offer between 5 and 10 years depending on the model. All our installations carry a 12-month workmanship guarantee. We register the manufacturer warranty on installation day. Annual servicing is required to keep the manufacturer warranty valid.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">GRANTS</span>&nbsp; Is there a free boiler grant available on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes, for eligible households. The ECO4 scheme funds boiler replacements for homeowners on qualifying benefits including Universal Credit, Pension Credit and Child Tax Credit. We assess your eligibility at the free survey. Wirral has a significant proportion of ECO4-eligible households, particularly across Birkenhead and Wallasey. See <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-great-british-insulation-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gov.uk</a> for eligibility details.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Wirral boiler installations?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our engineers are Gas Safe registered. Verify our registration at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. It is illegal to install a gas boiler without this registration. Gas Safe and Benchmark certificates are issued on installation day.</p></div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


